1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Bd3 dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 {
The b5 advance has freed the b7-square for our light-squared bishop.} 8. Bd3
Bb7 9. O-O {White plays safely.} a6 10. a4 {White tries to undermine Black's
pawn on b5.} b4 {A pesky advance.} 11. Ne4 {This is another possible
destination for White's knight.} c5 12. Ned2 {White avoids the trade of
knights.} Be7 {Black will castle next with a very sound position.} *

