a3 {The purpose of this move is simply to guard the b4 square so that Black
cannot attack White's knight on c3.} a6 {A common structure in the Semi-Slav
where Black is looking to play the freeing move c5.} 10. O-O c5 {Unleashing
the bishop on b7 and allowing for easy development.} 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. b4 Be7 {
On the a7-g1 diagonal, the bishop would stare at the pawn on e3, so Black
should retreat it to e7.} 13. Bb2 O-O {The position is very balanced, but
Black has a slight edge due to his slightly better placed knight on d7
compared to White's knight on c3.} *

