The b5 advance has freed the b7-square for our light-squared bishop.} 8. Bb3 {
This is another possible bishop retreat, but it is much less common. The
bishop is not idealy placed eyeing the e6-pawn.} b4 {An annoying move, hitting
the knight.} 9. Ne2 Bb7 10. O-O Bd6 11. Nf4 O-O 12. Ng5 {White is threatening
Bxe6 or Nxe6 ideas.} Bxf4 {Black gives up the bishop pair to remove one of the
dangerous knights and damage White's pawn structure.} 13. exf4 c5 {The freeing
move.} *

