1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Qc2 {This move defines
the Anti-Meran Variation. White's idea is to not commit the bishop immediately
so that if White takes on c4 he can recapture in one move.} Bd6 {Black
continues his development in normal fashion. Now White has many options which
will be explored in this chapter.} *

