1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Qc2 Bd6 7. Be2 {Usually
the bishop comes to Bd3. However, White can also choose to play Be2 if he
wants.} O-O 8. b3 {White supports his c4-pawn co that Black captures on c4, he
can recapture with the b3-pawn. We have now transposed to 7.b3 lines.} b6 {
Black frees the b7-square for his light-squared bishop. At the moment the
position looks very solid and uneventful, but it could open up at any time due
to some pawn trades in the center.} *

