yet another developing move White can choose on move 7.} O-O 8. Bd3 dxc4 {
Now that White's light-squared bishop has moved, Black should play the
thematic dxc4.} 9. Bxc4 b5 {This is the standard pawn push, vacating the
b7-square with tempo gain on the bishop.} 10. Bd3 Bb7 11. O-O a6 {Now we have
entered into a typical Semi-Slav position where Black can play for a c5 break
and bring his rooks to the center comfortably.} *

