fairly easy to play. White has given up the bishop pair early, which I find
very convenient.} Qxf6 {The recapture with the queen is much better than gxf6.}
7. g3 {This is another possible sideline. White wants to fianchetto on the
kingside.} Nd7 8. Bg2 dxc4 {Black should just grab the c4 pawn.} 9. O-O Be7 10.
Ne4 Qf5 {White has not created any problems for Black. Now Black needs to find
a way to bring his light-squared bishop into play and then open the position.
If he is able to do this, Black will have an edge due to his bishop pair. One
way of doing this would be to play b5 followed by Bb7 and eventually c5.} *

